> Our chef Victoria comes from Scotland, so she's using her favourite Scottish staple: smoked haddock. Locals from the fishing town of Finnan tuck into a bowl of warm poached Finnan Haddie (haddock, cold smoked over peat in Finnan) for brekkie! This dish is a gentler more fragrant version of this famous Scottish breakfast, served with some trusty crushed potato and delicious healthy greens.

Bring a large #pot of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cut the @New Potatoes{1}(bigger ones cut in half) (no need to peel) and pop them in your pot of boiling water to simmer for ~{15%minutes} or until cooked.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Place the @Smoked Haddock{2} in a #non-stick frying pan{}, season lightly with @black pepper{} and add the @Milk{150%ml}.

> Don't worry if your fish is not fully covered by the milk!

Simmer gently for ~{8-10%minutes} uncovered on medium-low heat. In the meantime, roughly chop the @Baby Spinach{1} and use #scissors to roughly chop the @Chives{1/2} into ½cm pieces.

Once your potatoes are cooked, drain them. Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in the same #pot on medium heat and throw your potatoes back in, together with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Lightly mash the mixture with the back of a #fork for about ~{30%seconds} or until your potatoes look crushed. Remove from the heat and cover to keep warm.

Heat a separate #frying pan on medium-high heat and add a glug of @oil{glug} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Throw in your spinach and stir for ~{30%seconds} or until wilted. Remove from the heat and cover.

Your fish should now be ready (opaque but not yet flaking). Remove it from the pan using a large #spatula and set aside. Add the @Creme Fraiche{1/2} to your pan and turn the heat up to high. Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes} uncovered, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, cut the @Lemon{1/2}(cut into wedges) into wedges. Now add the @Butter Salted{30%g} to your crème fraîche mix and whisk everything together, then return your fish to the pan. Pop your chives into the pan as well, together with a few grinds of @black pepper{few grinds}, and allow your creamy chivey fish to bubble for ~{30%seconds}.

Place a dollop of potato on your #plate, top with your creamy chivey fish and serve with your spinach and a wedge of lemon to squeeze over the top. Enjoy!